Attorney-General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami, SAN, has condoled with the families of the eight Nigerians of Kebbi State origin that lost their lives in a boat mishap at Tungar Geheru, Jega Local Government. In a statement issued by Dr. Umar Jibrilu Gwandu, Special Assistant on Media and Public Relations, Office of the Attorney-General of the Federation, Malami sympathised with the families of the deceased adding that he was grieved by the tragic incident. While praying for the reposed of the souls of the deceased, Malami who described the incident as unfortunate prayed for the speedy recovery of those rescued.